q.p:
Now I ſay the Heire as long as hee is a Child differeth nothing
from a ſervant, though he be Lord of all, but is under Tutors and Governours,
untill the time appointed of the Father.

list.item:
2. Reaſons taken from the very Nature of the High Court of Parliament,
both as it is the highest Court of Juſtice, and greateſt Councell of the Realme;
and from the importance of the publike affaires therein tranſacted.
